Garlic Ginger Chicken with Cilantro and Mint
  --Priya Krishna with Ritu Krishna
  
8 garlic cloves, finely chopped
3 tbsp fresh lemon juice (~1 lemon)
2 tbsp finely chopped fresh ginger
3 tbsp + 1 tsp evoo
1 tbsp finely chopped cilantro leaves + more for garnish
1 tbsp finely chopped mint leaves + more for garnish
1 tbsp ground coriander
1 tsp amchur 
1 tsp ground tumeric
3/4 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp red chili powder
4 skinless, boneless chicken breasts (1/2 - 3/4 lb each)

Mix garlic, ginger, lemon juice, 3 tbsp oil, cilantro, and min in a medium bowl to form a paste. Mix coriander, amchur, tumeric, salt, and chili powder in a small bowl. Add spice mixture to garlic paste and stir well to combine. Transfer marinade to large resealable bag. Place chicken in bag and seal tightly. Using hands, gently massage marinade onto chicken, making sure to evenly coat each breast. Chill 2 hrs. Heat a large skillet over medium high. Once pan is quite hot, add remaining oil, swirling pan to coat the entire surface. Reduce heat to medium. Remove chicken from marinade and cook, undisturbed, until lightly golden on one side, 1-2 min. Flip chicken and continue to cook until golden brown on the other side, 1-2 more min. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook without peeking 10 min. Remove pan from heat and let sit covered 10-15 min depending on thickenss of breasts. Check to make sure they are cooked through, instant read thermometer should register 165F. Transfer to cutting board and slice into strips. Transfer to a platter; garnish with cilantro and mint.



Notes: Can pound chicken to flatten. Can use cilantro stems too.
